ca.gc.ic.broadcast.entity.enumerated

Enum ECanadaStationClass

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ECanadaStationClass>
      • ca.gc.ic.broadcast.entity.enumerated.ECanadaStationClass
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ECanadaStationClass>

    public enum ECanadaStationClass
extends java.lang.Enum<ECanadaStationClass>
    An enumeration of the allowed 'CLASS' field values in the Canada station tables 'am_statio', 'fm_statio', 'tv_statio' and 'sdars'.

    To prevent Java language conflict the table field is named 'clazz' and the Java object (this) is named 'ECanadaStationClass'.

    Some classes are used across service types. For example. 'A' is used for AM, FM and TV stations.
